  "paragraphs": [
    {
      "para_id": "Q001060.2",
      "line_range": "2",
      "translation": "(i 4) ... Enlil demarcated ... for ( Ninĝirsu ) and Me-silim erected a stela , .... his order ...."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001060.8",
      "line_range": "8",
      "translation": "(ii 5) ... removed the stela and repositioned it towards the plain of Lagaš ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001060.12",
      "line_range": "12",
      "translation": "(iv 2) E-ana-tum , ruler of Lagaš , given strenght by Enlil , nourished on rich milk by Ninhursaĝa , called by a propitious name by Nanše , who makes the foreign lands submit to Ninĝirsu , returned his beloved field under Ninĝirsu’s authority . E-ana-tum did not let ( the field ) extend beyond the place where Me-silim once had erected the stela . He returned ( this stela ) to its ( original ) place ."
    }
  ],
